-->

## SYNOPSIS

`secure-terminal-cli` [`--mode` <MODE>] [<COMMAND> [<ARGS>...]]

## DESCRIPTION

secure-terminal-cli is the same safe core as `secure-terminal`(1) without the
GUI. It runs a command (or your login shell) in a pseudo-terminal and sanitizes
the program's output before it reaches your existing terminal: escape sequences
are removed and every byte that is not printable ASCII is neutralized, so a
crafted file, log or SSH banner cannot redraw the screen, move the cursor, set
the window title or touch the clipboard.

Unlike the GUI, it does not sanitize your keystrokes and does not run the paste
warning: it makes what a program *displays* safe, on a plain console or inside an
SSH session that has no access to the GUI. It does not sandbox the program you
run; if you choose to run something harmful, it runs, exactly as in any terminal.

## OPTIONS

  * `--mode` <MODE>:
    How to show non-ASCII output. `strip` (the safe default) replaces non-ASCII
    with `_`; `show` renders legitimate printable glyphs while still neutralizing
    the invisible, bidi and homoglyph classes; `reveal` shows every non-ASCII
    character as a `<U+XXXX>` badge.

  * <COMMAND> [<ARGS>...]:
    The command to run. With no command, your login shell is started.

  * `-h`, `--help`:
    Show a usage summary and exit.

